<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Services on Atlas</title><link>https://www.javiercd.es/en/tags/services/</link><description>Recent content in Services on Atlas</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 08 Sep 2023 10:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.javiercd.es/en/tags/services/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Installing and Configuring a DHCP Server on Linux</title><link>https://www.javiercd.es/en/posts/servicios/dhcp/instalacion_y_configuracion_de_un_servidor_dhcp_en_linux/dhcp_ipv4/</link><pubDate>Fri, 08 Sep 2023 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.javiercd.es/en/posts/servicios/dhcp/instalacion_y_configuracion_de_un_servidor_dhcp_en_linux/dhcp_ipv4/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="configuring-the-dhcp-server-on-debian"&gt;Configuring the DHCP Server on Debian&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this article, you will learn how to configure the &lt;code&gt;isc-dhcp-server&lt;/code&gt;. Additionally, we will configure an IP reservation and set it up to operate on two different scopes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is my DHCP server&amp;rsquo;s network configuration:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Router external network&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;auto ens4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;iface ens4 inet dhcp
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Internal network 1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;auto ens5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;iface ens5 inet static
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; address 192.168.10.1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; netmask 255.255.255.0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# SNAT for ens5 network , ensure that bit of forwarding is activated.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; post-up iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -o ens4 -j MASQUERADE
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; post-down iptables -t nat -D POSTROUTING -o ens4 -j MASQUERADE
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Internal network 2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;auto ens6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;iface ens6 inet static
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; address 192.168.20.1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; netmask 255.255.255.0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="installing-the-isc-dhcp-server"&gt;Installing the isc-dhcp-server&lt;/h2&gt;
